Gentoo provides several tools for managing network connections. If you have emerged OpenRc without network support, i.e. with both USE flags [https://packages.gentoo.org/useflags/netifrc <code>netifrc</code>] and [https://packages.gentoo.org/useflags/newnet <code>newnet</code>] disabled, you might need to set up a network manager such as [[netifrc|net-misc/netifrc]], [[Network_management_using_DHCPCD|net-misc/dhcpcd]], [[Wicd|net-misc/wicd]], [[NetworkManager|net-misc/networkmanager]], or {{Package|net-misc/badvpn}}. Or, you have the option of emerging openrc with the [https://packages.gentoo.org/useflags/newnet <code>newnet</code>] use flag and configuring {{Path|/etc/conf.d/network}} and {{Path|/etc/conf.d/staticroute}} if you only use static interfaces.<ref>[https://gitweb.gentoo.org/repo/gentoo.git/plain/sys-apps/openrc/openrc-9999.ebuild sys-apps/openrc-9999.ebuild]</ref>

